de.rwth.i2.attestor.semantics.jimpleSemantics.translation

Class TopLevelTranslation

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.rwth.i2.attestor.main.scene.SceneObject
      • de.rwth.i2.attestor.semantics.jimpleSemantics.translation.TopLevelTranslation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    JimpleToAbstractSemantics

    public class TopLevelTranslation
extends SceneObject
implements JimpleToAbstractSemantics
    This class organizes the actual translation process by splitting a Jimple program into methods and methods into units. The lower translation layers can ask this element for the pc of a given unit and the method-translation for a given method-signature.

    The translation process is started by translate().

    This class does not specify actual translation rules for statements/values/types. Those can be found in the translation hierarchy starting in firstLevel

    Author:
    Hannah Arndt, Christoph

      • translate

        public void translate()
        First fills the methodMapping with new abstractMethods for each method in the main class. Then fills these methods each with the corresponding translation of statements.
        Assumes that soot.Scene already containsSubsumingState the Jimple code that should be translated.
        See Also:
        translateMethod(SootMethod)
